Apartments



The compounding benefits of higher paying jobs entering the Southeast and S=
outhwest suggest rental pricing power in Sun Belt markets will likely be mo=
re durable than previously anticipated. However, not every Sun Belt and Coa=
stal market will benefit or struggle equally, as the quality of recent job =
and population gains vary by MSA.



*         Residential Insights -  Gentrification Snowball: https://my.green=
street.com/research/reports/16524/download?region=3DNA&applyWaterMark=3D1

o   A deep dive into recent job and population growth trends driven by migr=
ation patterns in recent years and the implications to growth moving forwar=
d.



[cid:image002.jpg@01D8D8F8.FB8424A0]

SFR



Green Street's relatively bullish single-family rental (SFR) M-RevPAF growt=
h estimates will likely remain unchanged (~6% growth per annum from '22-'26=
).  SFR is well positioned to capture an outsized share of both cross-state=
 and intra-market migration over the coming years as an aging millennial de=
mographic tilts more suburban within markets and Sun Belt markets capture a=
n outsized share of population growth.



*         Residential Insights - Resilient Rents; https://my.greenstreet.co=
m/research/reports/16483/download?region=3DNA&applyWaterMark=3D1

o   SFR top-line unchanged; ~6% ann. expense growth over next three years







[cid:image003.jpg@01D8D8F8.FB8424A0]



Office



Office observation decks offer attractive prospective returns, suggesting n=
ew observatories will be built; already happening in NYC & Boston.



*         Office Insights - Billion Dollar View: https://my.greenstreet.com=
/research/reports/16525/download?region=3DNA&applyWaterMark=3D1

o   The Observatory at the top of the Empire State Building (ESB) is a cash=
 cow

*         Office Sector - Boston Office Tour Takeaways

o   A tour of Boston's office and life science market coincided with Boston=
 Properties' investor day<https://my.greenstreet.com/research-library?regio=
n=3DNA&reportId=3Dqt_6191>, which provided an opportunity to check in on th=
e city's office/lab markets and Green Street's current underwriting assumpt=
ions. High-level takeaways are summarized herein.

o   Direction for office values across most markets, including Boston, is l=
ower. Green Street estimates that Boston office values have fallen ~5% this=
 year, while the gateway average has fallen ~7%.

*         Property Insights - Grid 101: https://my.greenstreet.com/research=
/reports/16526/download?region=3DNA&applyWaterMark=3D1

o   As green building regulations increase, power grids are an underappreci=
ated part of the ESG puzzle. Both building energy use and the "greenness" o=
f the underlying electric grid determine building emissions. More pollutive=
 grids pose risk to landlords as net-zero costs are likely to be absorbed d=
irectly or indirectly over time



