Self Storage

Move-in activity has moderated (in some cases has decreased from normal act=
ivity) while move-outs have rapidly increased from subdued levels observed =
in '20 and '21. As such, occupancy is moderating faster than anticipated an=
d appears poised to reach 'normal' levels by late-'23.



The move to digital rental and increased automation has both improved the c=
ustomer experience and operating margins. It is clear that operators that d=
o not offer digital options for renters are likely to fall behind peers.



*         Self-Storage Conference Insight: An Evolving Experience: https://=
my.greenstreet.com/research/reports/16517/download?region=3DNA&applyWaterMa=
rk=3D1

o   Green Street recently attended (in person) the Self-Storage Association=
 (SSA) Fall Conference held in Las Vegas.



[cid:image009.jpg@01D8D8F8.FB8424A0]



Lodging



While the segment is due for a near-term course correction, Green Street fo=
recasts RevPAR to exceed pre-Covid levels by ~25% in '26. This implies an o=
verall '19-'26 RevPAR growth rate roughly in line with that experienced in =
the years preceding the pandemic.  Said another way, Covid appears to have =
pulled forward several years of growth into a short window of time.



